								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">20</div> <div class="vers-content">Ideo hÃ¦c dicit Dominus Deus: Ecce furor meus et indignatio mea conflatur super locum istum, super viros, et super jumenta, et super lignum regionis, et super fruges terrÃ¦: et succendetur, et non extinguetur.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">20</div> <div class="vers-content">Therefore thus saith the Lord God: Behold my wrath and my indignation is enkindled against this place, upon men and upon beasts, and upon the trees of the field, and upon the fruits of the land, and it shall burn, and shall not be quenched.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">20</div> <div class="vers-content">This warning, then, the Lord God sends them: Fury and indignation of mine are brewing against this place, man and beast, woodland tree and growing crop; and when that fire is lit, there shall be no quenching it.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">21</div> <div class="vers-content">HÃ¦c dicit Dominus exercituum, Deus IsraÃ«l: Holocautomata vestra addite victimis vestris, et comedite carnes:</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">21</div> <div class="vers-content">Thus saith the Lord of hosts the God of Israel: Add your burnt offerings to your sacrifices, and eat ye the flesh.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">21</div> <div class="vers-content">A message from the Lord of hosts, the God of Israel: No more be at pains to distinguish between burnt-sacrifice and offering; use for your own eating the flesh of all alike!</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">22</div> <div class="vers-content">quia non sum locutus cum patribus vestris, et non prÃ¦cepi eis, in die qua eduxi eos de terra Ã†gypti, de verbo holocautomatum et victimarum:</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">22</div> <div class="vers-content">For I spoke not to your fathers, and I commanded them not, in the day that I brought them out of the land of Egypt, concerning the matter of burnt offerings and sacrifices.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">22</div> <div class="vers-content">Burnt-sacrifices, offerings, not of these was my theme when I gave commandments to your fathers at the time of their deliverance from Egypt; </div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">23</div> <div class="vers-content">sed hoc verbum prÃ¦cepi eis, dicens: Audite vocem meam, et ero vobis Deus, et vos eritis mihi populus: et ambulate in omni via quam mandavi vobis, ut bene sit vobis.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">23</div> <div class="vers-content">But this thing I commanded them, saying: Hearken to my voice, and I will be your God, and you shall be my people: and walk ye in all the way that I have commanded you, that it may be well with you.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">23</div> <div class="vers-content">my word of command to them was, Obey my bidding, if I am to be your God, you my people; follow the path I have marked out for you, as you hope to prosper.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">24</div> <div class="vers-content">Et non audierunt, nec inclinaverunt aurem suam: sed abierunt in voluntatibus et in pravitate cordis sui mali: factique sunt retrorsum, et non in ante,</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">24</div> <div class="vers-content">But they hearkened not, nor inclined their ear: but walked in their own will, and in the perversity of their wicked heart: and went backward and not forward,</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">24</div> <div class="vers-content">And did they listen? Hearing they gave me none; their own whim, the false aim of their corrupt hearts was all the rule they lived by; still turned their backs on me, and refused to look my way;</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">25</div> <div class="vers-content">a die qua egressi sunt patres eorum de terra Ã†gypti usque ad diem hanc. Et misi ad vos omnes servos meos prophetas per diem, consurgens diluculo, et mittens:</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">25</div> <div class="vers-content">From the day that their fathers came out of the land of Egypt, even to this day. And I have sent to you all my servants the prophets from day to day, rising up early and sending.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">25</div> <div class="vers-content">so it has been since your fathers left Egypt, so it is yet. No day dawned but I was at work betimes, sending my servants to prophesy to them,</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">26</div> <div class="vers-content">et non audierunt me, nec inclinaverunt aurem suam: sed induraverunt cervicem suam, et pejus operati sunt quam patres eorum.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">26</div> <div class="vers-content">And they have not hearkened to me: nor inclined their ear: but have hardened their neck, and have done worse than their fathers.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">26</div> <div class="vers-content">but still they would not listen, still hearing they gave me none; stubborn under my yoke, they outdid their own fathers in wickedness.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">27</div> <div class="vers-content">Et loqueris ad eos omnia verba hÃ¦c, et non audient te: et vocabis eos, et non respondebunt tibi.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">27</div> <div class="vers-content">And thou shalt speak to them all these words, but they will not hearken to thee: and thou shalt call them, but they will not answer thee.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">27</div> <div class="vers-content">All this thou shalt say to them, but they will not listen to thee; thy call shall go unheeded.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">28</div> <div class="vers-content">Et dices ad eos: HÃ¦c est gens quÃ¦ non audivit vocem Domini Dei sui, nec recepit disciplinam; periit fides, et ablata est de ore eorum.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">28</div> <div class="vers-content">And thou shalt say to them: This is a nation which hath not hearkened to the voice of the Lord their God, nor received instruction: faith is lost, and is taken away out of their mouth.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">28</div> <div class="vers-content">Then tell them, Here is a people who will not listen to the voice of their own God, or accept reproof from him; loyalty is dead, the word is on their lips no more.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">29</div> <div class="vers-content">Tonde capillum tuum, et projice, et sume in directum planctum: quia projecit Dominus et reliquit generationem furoris sui;</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">29</div> <div class="vers-content">Cut off thy hair, and cast it away: and take up a lamentation on high: for the Lord hath rejected, and forsaken the generation of his wrath,</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">29</div> <div class="vers-content">Cut off, Jerusalem,  those locks of thine, and cast them away from thee; loud let the hills echo with thy lament; on a guilty age, the Lord has pronounced sentence of banishment and rejection.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">30</div> <div class="vers-content">quia fecerunt filii Juda malum in oculis meis, dicit Dominus. Posuerunt offendicula sua in domo in qua invocatum est nomen meum, ut polluerent eam:</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">30</div> <div class="vers-content">Because the children of Juda have done evil in my eyes, saith the Lord. They have set their abominations in the house in which my name is called upon, to pollute it;</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">30</div> <div class="vers-content">The men of Juda have defied my will, the Lord says; foul idols they have set up in the house that is the sanctuary of my name, and utterly profaned it;</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">31</div> <div class="vers-content">et Ã¦dificaverunt excelsa Topheth, quÃ¦ est in valle filii Ennom, ut incenderent filios suos et filias suas igni, quÃ¦ non prÃ¦cepi, nec cogitavi in corde meo.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">31</div> <div class="vers-content">And they have built the high places of Topheth, which is in the valley of the son of Ennom, to burn their sons, and their daughters in the fire: which I commanded not, nor thought on in my heart.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">31</div> <div class="vers-content">in the valley of Ben-Ennom stands the hill-shrine of Topheth, where they sacrifice their own sons and daughters in the furnace, a rite not of my bidding, not of my imagining.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">32</div> <div class="vers-content">Ideo ecce dies venient, dicit Dominus, et non dicetur amplius Topheth, et vallis filii Ennom, sed vallis interfectionis: et sepelient in Topheth, eo quod non sit locus.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">32</div> <div class="vers-content">Therefore behold the days shall come, saith the Lord, and it shall no more be called Topheth, nor the valley of the son of Ennom: but the valley of slaughter: and they shall bury in Topheth, because there is no place.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">32</div> <div class="vers-content">And now, the Lord says, a time is coming when no more will be heard of Topheth or Ben-Ennom; it will be called The Valley of the Slain; men will be finding room for their dead in Topheth, because other burying-ground is none.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">33</div> <div class="vers-content">Et erit morticinum populi hujus in cibos volucribus cÃ¦li et bestiis terrÃ¦, et non erit qui abigat.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">33</div> <div class="vers-content">And the carcasses of this people shall be meat for the fowls of the air, and for the beasts of the earth, and there shall be none to drive them away.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">33</div> <div class="vers-content">Nay, Juda shall be carrion for birds that fly in air, for beasts that roam the earth; and never a man left to drive them away.</div></div></td>
								</tr><tr>									<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">34</div> <div class="vers-content">Et quiescere faciam de urbibus Juda, et de plateis Jerusalem, vocem gaudii et vocem lÃ¦titiÃ¦, vocem sponsi et vocem sponsÃ¦: in desolationem enim erit terra.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">34</div> <div class="vers-content">And I will cause to cease out of the cities of Juda, and out of the streets of Jerusalem, the voice of joy, and the voice of gladness, the voice of the bridegroom and the voice of the bride: for the land shall be desolate.</div></div></td>
																	<td><div class="vers"><div class="vers-no">34</div> <div class="vers-content">In the townships of Juda, in the streets of Jerusalem, cries of joy and mirth shall be heard no more, voice of bridegroom and of bride shall be heard no more; the whole land will have turned into a wilderness.</div></div></td>
